This paper deals with the development of an optimal controller for a mechanical system, specifically the Furuta pendulum. This involves the use of Bayesian optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The system being controlled is a rotary inverted pendulum, which is a type of robot (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of energy-based control, which is a common approach in control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulations and experiments, which are common in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
